race.comment: PERILOUS LASS (9) looked sharp early at Gawler before fading late. Form around her is measuring up. Up in trip today for the first time, but if she can lead and dictate to her liking, then she'll be very hard to run down. MATINO (4) didn't fire last start but was a 30-1 chance there at Strathalbyn. Looks better placed here today with Murtagh hopping on board and if he can negotiate the sticky barrier, he'll go close. KING EDWARD (2) has been plain in two runs back but third-up and blinkers going on could spark improvement. STARGENT (5) was always rearward at Penola but did make some ground late. Extra distance helps and he's not the worst.
